    cabinetSupplyChainPara: "Houston cabinet supply runs through Cabinet Innovations in the Heights, Carrollton Cabinet Source, and Bayshore Fine Cabinetry in Kemah. Semi-custom KraftMaid and Medallion come through Home Depot Pro and Lowes Pro. Custom shops including Cabinet Works in Stafford and Signature Custom Cabinetry in The Woodlands build on 8-12 week lead times. IKEA Houston in the Galleria area supplies most Heights and Montrose budget remodels.",
    countertopTrendsPara: "Granite is still the Houston default because of the local fabrication industry in Stafford and Pasadena and because humidity does not damage properly sealed granite the way it cracks quartz seams. Ant Granite, Custom Granite, and Levantina Houston stock the slab yards. Quartz is gaining in Memorial and River Oaks through Caesarstone and Silestone. Leathered granite is a Houston-specific preference for hiding water spotting under humid conditions.",
    plumbingAndWaterPara: "Houston water is hard and chloraminated; the City of Houston Public Utilities draws from the Trinity River and Lake Houston. Post-tensioned slab homes require ground-penetrating radar or X-ray before any plumbing relocation through the slab, which adds $600-$1,500 to a sink move. Master plumbers (TSBPE-licensed) charge $110-$160/hour and the licensing is rigorously enforced. Pier-and-beam Heights houses allow easy underside access that cuts plumbing relocation cost in half.",
